# Shared agent setup

- Treat [AGENTS.md](mdc:AGENTS.md) as the canonical shared repo instructions and read the closest package-local `AGENTS.md` before editing package code.
- Use the verification matrix and command guidance in [AGENTS.md](mdc:AGENTS.md) instead of inventing tool-specific workflows.
- Use `bash scripts/codex/setup.sh` as the shared repo bootstrap for agent environments when the tool supports a project install/setup command.
- Start `pnpm run dev`, `pnpm run dev:web`, or other long-running services only when the task needs them.
- `pnpm run dx` and `pnpm run dx-f` are destructive reset flows, not default bootstrap commands.
